Can anyone give me tips on how to solo at the mid levels and some good places to do it?<br>
What are the best spells to use?<br>
<br>
Surely it is more efficient to kill in groups??<br>
 <p>------
Endurance</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=elrond>elrond</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://eonwethewizard.homestead.com/files/e.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/13/01 11:17:14 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://eonwethewizard.homestead.com/files/pic.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How do I solo???</span><hr size=1> Never solod??? Oh my, where to start....<br>
Well at lvl 29 you got bonds of force. This spell slows down mobs. Its ae so be careful with it. Use it to pull a mob. Run til you're out of range, turn around and cast your best nuke. Repeat until mob is dead. This is called &quot;kiting&quot;. I would suggest you get sow to speed this process up. And watch out, if bonds is resisted you will need sow to run away so you can root the mob. <br>
<br>
I think at your level I fought in FM giants fort in group. Then a few levels later moved to ledge in OT and kited solo there.<br>
<br>
If you can afford to pay for breeze or clarity regularly when you solo you will notice soloing can be more effecient then grouping. You don't have to share exp when you solo and unlike other caster classes we don't even have to share exp with our pets (which we don't have of course).<br>
<br>
If you can afford sow regularly when you solo, you will never die. Whereas in groups when you have tanks pulling like maniacs even when the cleric tells them to slow down, you just might die and in a not so great a place.<br>
 <p>              <img src="http://eonwethewizard.homestead.com/files/sig.jpg" border="0"
></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaephire.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aephire</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/13/01 11:22:19 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How do I solo???</span><hr size=1> At 30, I soloed the goblin headmaster in OOT, evil eggs in Gorge at the throne, aviak avocets in SK and probably a few other things.<br>
<br>
I basically would root and nuke most things.  Eggs died to me in two blasts (i'd only occasionally get exp but it was good and I was there mainly for the PBB hehe ).  Avocets were rough due to adds but if you can get SoW, pull them away, root, Bonds of Force, then nuke.  You can re-root or kite them when root breaks.<br>
<br>
For soloing, you'll root and/or snare with Bonds of Force and nuke hard and fast.  Learning how to use Bonds without snaring yourself is key here. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><center>
<b>Aephire Thundersoul</b><br>
<a href=http://pub3.ezboard.com/bhawkwoodscompanions>Hawkwood's Legion</a><br>
Wizard of 46 Evocations<br>
on Rodcet Nife
</center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/udanenel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Danenel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/13/01 12:13:31 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How do I solo???</span><hr size=1> When I was level 29, I bought SoW's from druids in SK and solo'd the Aviak Avocets... I clearly remember getting a FULL BLUE per kill. It was enough I spend level 30 there as well (to get through Hell). Typically lower groups camp there and they can't take the avocets so some of them I found, would donate sow's for me to keep the avocets cleared from the spawns.<br>
<br>
PS: I started solo'ing hardcore at level 16 on Scarecrows in WK.<br>
<br>
-Danenel Plasmaweaver<br>
L47 Wizard, Tholuxe Paells<br>
Gathering of Ancients<br>
 <p><b>Then with terrible strength, he spoke. They paled at his words, for it was if death had become incarnate and had spoken. Echoing throughout the stadium were the words of Danenel: "Tremble and Despair for I am power!"</b>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uennyaorcsbane.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ennya Orcsbane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/13/01 1:07:34 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How do I solo???</span><hr size=1> Look, there is only 4 good places I found for soloing at 29:<br>
&quot;A skeleton&quot; in Najena -- got nurfed, only 1 left. 2/3 blue for this guy. Root and nuke. Boreing camp, and it really irritates the people trying to get ghoulbane.<br>
<br>
(crypt of)Dalnir solo the zoneline. Nibblers preferred. Watch out for the Harm Touching MOBS, and the Coerced Gnome Female. ENSTILL the pet and nukewar.<br>
As fast as you can heal, and get mana back you can hunt.<br>
<br>
Ancient Croc camp in Upper Guk -- If there are people campe here, it's ususally for the ancient croc and they could care less about the Slatwater Crocs. GREAT exp, timer'd spawn, and the campers are usually bored silly and will help. As a bonus, the saltwater crocs drop one of the runes for the Runescale cloak.<br>
<br>
Firescale Croc in Lavastorm -- Timerd spawn, BoF if you can then nuke away. Run it to Najena, get your mana back and see #1 above *evil grin* half a blue on this one. Bonus: ANOTHER of the scales you need for runescale cloak. <p>Ennya Orcsbane<BR>
1st Elder of The Tears Of Veeshan<BR>
Achieved Slayer<BR>
Assigner of the Hunt<BR>
Wizardess<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=berdug0>berdug0</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/14/01 6:21:27 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How do I solo???</span><hr size=1> How to solo at level 30.<br>
<br>
4 must have spells to mem.<br>
<br>
Root/Enstill (I prefer root for fast casting time, some Enstill you decide).<br>
Bonds of Force<br>
Yonder<br>
Gate<br>
<br>
The other 4... up to you.  As long as one of them is your best nuke.<br>
<br>
Without sow, I pull with bonds of force.  If it sticks.. great.. run, stop and turn slightly, nuke... repeat.<br>
<br>
If Bonds of Force resists... root, backup if root sticks, Bonds.<br>
<br>
If everything gets resisted: Bonds and root.. Yonder... Yonder... Yonder... Gate.<br>
<br>
This is for single pulls only.<br>
<br>
If you have sow, bonds only once... if it resists the first time... screw it.. and just run and nuke.<br>
<br>
Where to solo.  LOIO sarnaks are good till 31.  31 thru 34 SK gnolls.  That should keep you busy for the next week or so. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/urashakra.showPublicProfile?language=EN>rashakra</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/16/01 9:53:18 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.proactusa.com/images/lettuce.jpeg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How do I solo???</span><hr size=1> when I was 30, I was quadding the Lake of Ill Omen Goblin 4 spawn at the NW corner of the lake.  Easy pull, easy kills.<br>
